<br />

<IMG hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/DOC_logo.jpg" width=150 height=159>The 2011 International CES is a proud participant in the U.S. Commercial Service’s International Buyer Program (IBP). In addition to providing one-on-one export counseling and matchmaking on-site at the show, the Commercial Service is hosting a free webcast on two of the fastest growing consumer electronics (CE) markets in the world: China and Brazil. Learn how to get your CE products into these markets and expand your global sales. Officials from the Department of Commerce will discuss U.S.-China and U.S.-Brazil trade relationships; hot topics in the two markets’ IT/consumer electronics sector; protecting your intellectual property; and much more!&nbsp;<BR><BR> This webcast will take place on Wednesday, July 21 from 2-3 p.m. EST. <BR>&nbsp;<BR><A href="https://emenuapps.ita.doc.gov/ePublic/newWebinarRegistration.jsp?SmartCode=0QAK" target=_blank>Register now</A>!<BR>
